Israeli Stocks: Ampal-American Israel, Given Imaging, Hot

-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 
2011-09-11T14:22:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-11/israeli-stocks-ampal-american-israel-given-imaging-hot.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index declined to
the lowest level since November 2009, retreating 3.6 percent to
1,024.93 at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv . Investors traded
about 1.11 billion shekels ($300 million) of shares and
convertible securities today, according to Tel Aviv Stock
Exchange data.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Ampal-American Israel (AMPL)  Corp, which has a stake in
the company that supplies gas from  Egypt , slumped to the lowest
on record, declining 8 percent to 1.286 shekels. Egypt’s ruling
military council declared a state of emergency to restore order
after protesters attacked the Israeli embassy in Cairo.  Given Imaging Ltd. (GIVN)  , a manufacturer of pill-sized
cameras for digestive diagnosis, retreated to the lowest level
since Aug. 24, falling 3.8 percent to 51.71 shekels. The U.S.
traded shares dropped to a one-year low on Sept. 9 on concern a
global economic slowdown and cuts U.S. healthcare spending will
reduce demand for the company’s pill-sized cameras for digestive
diagnosis.  Hot Telecommunication System Ltd. (HOT)   advanced to the
highest level in almost a week, rising 2.2 percent to 47.09
shekels. The cable-service provider received changes to the
structure of the purchase for MIRS Communication Ltd. which
lowers the value of the deal to 1.2 billion shekels from 1.3
billion shekels. Separately, Hot said it received regulatory
approval for the merger.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
